    "description": {
      "value": "<h2>Biology and Appearance</h2><p>The parwan species are tall and gangly, with arms ending in three-fingered hands. They also have four dangling tentacles on the lower half of their bodies. They have three eyes and a mushroom-like head. Parwans have a unique physiology in that their bodies are essentially ambulatory bags of gas, which makes them lighter than air. The species can float on wind currents, and use their tentacles and arms to tether themselves to the ground.</p><p>The species also produce a naturally high electrical field, and crackle with the energy their bodies produces. Parwan can withstand high levels of electric power, and liquids, though the degree of how powerful this resistance is depend on the species' two different blood types.</p><h2>Society and Culture</h2><p>Parwans are a species dedicated to their craft. Whether it is bioengineering, mercenary work, or collecting model starfighters, parwans dedicate themselves wholly to their trade. This has often led to mockery, as parwans can become somewhat obsessed, collecting vast amounts of knowledge about their personal calling. Society on their homeworld of Parwa is highly regimented, with a majority of parwan life being laid out for them from birth until death. Because of this, a large majority of parwans find themselves leaving their homeworld in search of a life where they can be free to pursue their own career.</p><h2>Names</h2><p>While generally easy to pronounce, parwan names are infamous for sounding odd to outsiders. Whenever asked, parwans exhibit confusion, as their names are considered typical in their own language. They use agendered names without surnames.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>First Names.</strong> Corbuldin, Gerachu, Jekoono, Perotkin</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
